race.comment: Tough race. SHE FLYS (8) is going okay for this, beaten narrowly in a stronger race at Kilmore last time out when fourth in a BM56. Comes back a notch here, she draws beautifully and can notch up that elusive second win. CHOSEN VENTURE (1) will find this much easier than last start at Seymour in a BM62, sent around a $9 chance there but struggling. His best form has been here on his home deck with 4 of his 5 career wins on the circuit. He rates highly and should go close. CORTAIN (6) doesn't win out of turn but wasn't far away last start at Echuca and draws nicely. Each way. FINAL QUARTER (11) is stuck on the 1 career win but knocking on the door of another, placing in her past three. Back in trip here but should be hard to hold out. SHARE THE DREAM (2) comes back in trip off a first up run which is an interesting set up, not discounting the stable.
